### SEC filing extraction

Implement deterministic filing extraction:

* Fetch SEC filing index JSON and primary document.
* Store raw HTML/text.
* Convert to normalized text.
* Extract sections by item number and heading regex.
* Store section boundaries and extraction confidence.
* If extraction confidence is low, store the full document link and mark the section low-confidence/unavailable.

For equities:

* 10-K: Items 1, 1A, 2, 3, 7, 7A, 8, 9A
* 10-Q: Items 1, 1A, 2, 3, 4
* 20-F: business, risk factors, operating and financial review, directors/senior management, major shareholders, financial statements when extractable

For ETFs/funds:

* investment objective
* fees and expenses
* principal investment strategy
* principal risks
* portfolio holdings
* distributions and taxes
* purchase/redemption
* index methodology where disclosed
* securities lending where disclosed

